title: MAN IN THE MOON
tips: - Shift to rest the tail bone on the bottom bar and press one shoulder against the side of the lyra
- Press one foot against the opposite side of the lyra; move the other foot under the first foot and press it against that side of the lyra
variations: - Press the balls of the feet aginst the side of the lyra instead of pressing flat feet
- Straighten the legs and cross the ankles so that the tops of the feet press against the front and back of the lyra

title: PIKE UNDER THE BAR
tips: - Start under the bar or from a knee hang
- Do an inverted tuck under the bar, then straighten the legs and point the toes
- Lift the hips up - don't let the body sag
